  23:Drivers/STM32U5xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32u5xx_hal_flash_ex.c ****                    ##### Flash Extended features #####
  24:Drivers/STM32U5xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32u5xx_hal_flash_ex.c ****  ==============================================================================
  25:Drivers/STM32U5xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32u5xx_hal_flash_ex.c **** 
  26:Drivers/STM32U5xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32u5xx_hal_flash_ex.c ****   [..] Comparing to other previous devices, the FLASH interface for STM32U5xx
  27:Drivers/STM32U5xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32u5xx_hal_flash_ex.c ****        devices contains the following additional features
  28:Drivers/STM32U5xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32u5xx_hal_flash_ex.c **** 
  29:Drivers/STM32U5xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32u5xx_hal_flash_ex.c ****        (+) Capacity up to 2 Mbyte with dual bank architecture supporting read-while-write
ARM GAS  /tmp/ccjaol5C.s 			page 2


  30:Drivers/STM32U5xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32u5xx_hal_flash_ex.c ****            capability (RWW)
  31:Drivers/STM32U5xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32u5xx_hal_flash_ex.c ****        (+) Dual bank memory organization
  32:Drivers/STM32U5xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32u5xx_hal_flash_ex.c ****        (+) Watermark-based secure area including the secure hide areas
  33:Drivers/STM32U5xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32u5xx_hal_flash_ex.c ****        (+) Block-based secure pages
  34:Drivers/STM32U5xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32u5xx_hal_flash_ex.c **** 
  35:Drivers/STM32U5xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32u5xx_hal_flash_ex.c ****                         ##### How to use this driver #####
  36:Drivers/STM32U5xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32u5xx_hal_flash_ex.c ****  ==============================================================================
  37:Drivers/STM32U5xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32u5xx_hal_flash_ex.c ****   [..] This driver provides functions to configure and program the FLASH memory
  38:Drivers/STM32U5xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32u5xx_hal_flash_ex.c ****        of all STM32U5xx devices. It includes:
  39:Drivers/STM32U5xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32u5xx_hal_flash_ex.c ****       (#) Flash Memory Erase functions:
  40:Drivers/STM32U5xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32u5xx_hal_flash_ex.c ****            (++) Lock and Unlock the FLASH interface using HAL_FLASH_Unlock() and
  41:Drivers/STM32U5xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32u5xx_hal_flash_ex.c ****                 HAL_FLASH_Lock() functions
  42:Drivers/STM32U5xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32u5xx_hal_flash_ex.c ****            (++) Erase function: page Erase and Bank/Mass Erase
  43:Drivers/STM32U5xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32u5xx_hal_flash_ex.c ****            (++) There are two modes of erase :
  44:Drivers/STM32U5xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32u5xx_hal_flash_ex.c ****              (+++) Polling Mode using HAL_FLASHEx_Erase()
  45:Drivers/STM32U5xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32u5xx_hal_flash_ex.c ****              (+++) Interrupt Mode using HAL_FLASHEx_Erase_IT()
  46:Drivers/STM32U5xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32u5xx_hal_flash_ex.c **** 
  47:Drivers/STM32U5xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32u5xx_hal_flash_ex.c ****       (#) Option Bytes Programming function: Use HAL_FLASHEx_OBProgram() to:
  48:Drivers/STM32U5xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32u5xx_hal_flash_ex.c ****         (++) Configure the write protection for each area
  49:Drivers/STM32U5xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32u5xx_hal_flash_ex.c ****         (++) Set the Read protection Level
  50:Drivers/STM32U5xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32u5xx_hal_flash_ex.c ****         (++) Program the user Option Bytes
  51:Drivers/STM32U5xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32u5xx_hal_flash_ex.c ****         (++) Configure the watermark security for each area including the secure hide areas
  52:Drivers/STM32U5xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32u5xx_hal_flash_ex.c ****         (++) Configure the boot lock (BOOT_LOCK)
  53:Drivers/STM32U5xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32u5xx_hal_flash_ex.c ****         (++) Configure the Boot addresses
  54:Drivers/STM32U5xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32u5xx_hal_flash_ex.c **** 
  55:Drivers/STM32U5xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32u5xx_hal_flash_ex.c ****       (#) Get Option Bytes Configuration function: Use HAL_FLASHEx_OBGetConfig() to:
  56:Drivers/STM32U5xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32u5xx_hal_flash_ex.c ****         (++) Get the value of a write protection area
  57:Drivers/STM32U5xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32u5xx_hal_flash_ex.c ****         (++) Know if the read protection is activated
  58:Drivers/STM32U5xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32u5xx_hal_flash_ex.c ****         (++) Get the value of the user Option Bytes
  59:Drivers/STM32U5xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32u5xx_hal_flash_ex.c ****         (++) Get the configuration of a watermark security area including the secure hide areas
  60:Drivers/STM32U5xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32u5xx_hal_flash_ex.c ****         (++) Get the boot lock (BOOT_LOCK) configuration
  61:Drivers/STM32U5xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32u5xx_hal_flash_ex.c ****         (++) Get the value of a boot address
  62:Drivers/STM32U5xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32u5xx_hal_flash_ex.c **** 
  63:Drivers/STM32U5xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32u5xx_hal_flash_ex.c ****       (#) Block-based secure / privilege area configuration function: Use HAL_FLASHEx_ConfigBBAttri
  64:Drivers/STM32U5xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32u5xx_hal_flash_ex.c ****         (++) Bit-field allowing to secure or un-secure each page
  65:Drivers/STM32U5xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32u5xx_hal_flash_ex.c ****         (++) Bit-field allowing to privilege or un-privilege each page
  66:Drivers/STM32U5xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32u5xx_hal_flash_ex.c **** 
  67:Drivers/STM32U5xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32u5xx_hal_flash_ex.c ****       (#) Get the block-based secure / privilege area configuration function: Use HAL_FLASHEx_GetBB
  68:Drivers/STM32U5xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32u5xx_hal_flash_ex.c ****         (++) Return the configuration of the block-based security and privilege for all the pages
  69:Drivers/STM32U5xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32u5xx_hal_flash_ex.c **** 
  70:Drivers/STM32U5xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32u5xx_hal_flash_ex.c ****       (#) Activation of the secure hide area function: Use HAL_FLASHEx_EnableSecHideProtection()
  71:Drivers/STM32U5xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32u5xx_hal_flash_ex.c ****         (++) Deny the access to the secure hide area
  72:Drivers/STM32U5xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32u5xx_hal_flash_ex.c **** 
  73:Drivers/STM32U5xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32u5xx_hal_flash_ex.c ****       (#) Privilege mode configuration function: Use HAL_FLASHEx_ConfigPrivMode()
  74:Drivers/STM32U5xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32u5xx_hal_flash_ex.c ****         (++) FLASH register can be protected against non-privilege accesses
  75:Drivers/STM32U5xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32u5xx_hal_flash_ex.c **** 
  76:Drivers/STM32U5xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32u5xx_hal_flash_ex.c ****       (#) Get the privilege mode configuration function: Use HAL_FLASHEx_GetPrivMode()
  77:Drivers/STM32U5xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32u5xx_hal_flash_ex.c ****         (++) Return if the FLASH registers are protected against non-privilege accesses
  78:Drivers/STM32U5xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32u5xx_hal_flash_ex.c **** 
  79:Drivers/STM32U5xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32u5xx_hal_flash_ex.c ****       (#) Security inversion configuration function: Use HAL_FLASHEx_ConfigSecInversion()
  80:Drivers/STM32U5xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32u5xx_hal_flash_ex.c ****         (++) FLASH secure state can be override
  81:Drivers/STM32U5xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32u5xx_hal_flash_ex.c **** 
  82:Drivers/STM32U5xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32u5xx_hal_flash_ex.c ****       (#) Get the security inversion configuration function: Use HAL_FLASHEx_GetSecInversion()
  83:Drivers/STM32U5xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32u5xx_hal_flash_ex.c ****         (++) Return if FLASH secure state is override
  84:Drivers/STM32U5xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32u5xx_hal_flash_ex.c **** 
  85:Drivers/STM32U5xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32u5xx_hal_flash_ex.c ****       (#) Enable bank low-power mode function: Use HAL_FLASHEx_EnablePowerDown()
  86:Drivers/STM32U5xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32u5xx_hal_flash_ex.c ****         (++) Enable low-power mode for Flash Bank 1 and/or Bank 2
ARM GAS  /tmp/ccjaol5C.s 			page 3


  87:Drivers/STM32U5xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32u5xx_hal_flash_ex.c **** 
  88:Drivers/STM32U5xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32u5xx_hal_flash_ex.c ****       (#) Enable low-power read mode function: Use HAL_FLASHEx_ConfigLowPowerRead()
  89:Drivers/STM32U5xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32u5xx_hal_flash_ex.c ****         (++) Enable low-power read mode for Flash memory
  90:Drivers/STM32U5xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32u5xx_hal_flash_ex.c **** 
  91:Drivers/STM32U5xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32u5xx_hal_flash_ex.c ****       (#) Get the low-power read mode configuration function: Use HAL_FLASHEx_GetLowPowerRead()
  92:Drivers/STM32U5xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32u5xx_hal_flash_ex.c ****         (++) Return if FLASH is in low-power read mode or normal read mode
